24:06.360 --> 24:10.140
1980 was a successful year for Science Fiction author George Martin.

24:10.620 --> 24:14.260
Martin received the Hugo Award for his short story, The Way of Cross and Dragon,

24:14.580 --> 24:17.960
and both the Hugo and Nebula Awards for his novelette, Sand Kings.

24:18.460 --> 24:22.320
Sand Kings is one of those timeless stories that is destined to be a classic.

24:22.880 --> 24:25.520
In 1981, the novel Windhaven was published.

24:25.520 --> 24:28.680
It was written by Martin in conjunction with Lisa Tuttle.

25:01.700 --> 25:02.220
We learned that Windhaven as a novel was not the original intent of Martin and Tuttle.

25:02.220 --> 25:06.060
The first writer would rewrite the portion the second writer had gone on,

25:06.100 --> 25:08.540
so each of us essentially rewrote the other one's sections,

25:08.900 --> 25:15.060
and we alternated doing the first drafts after having worked out the bullet outlines of the plot together in conference.

25:16.300 --> 25:18.060
It took place through the mail.

25:18.820 --> 25:23.200
We learned that Windhaven as a novel was not the original intent of Martin and Tuttle.

25:23.200 --> 25:25.420
Rather, it started out as a shorter story.

25:26.120 --> 25:31.640
Actually, it began as a much shorter story, a thing called My Brother's Wings that we completed in collaboration.

25:32.400 --> 25:35.680
It showed it to Ben Boven. He said, it doesn't really end satisfactorily.

25:36.020 --> 25:38.160
It needs to be much longer, and he was right.

25:38.500 --> 25:41.680
We went back and we expanded it and we produced the storms at Windhaven.

25:42.140 --> 25:49.620
But I think by the time we finished that, it was pretty clear to us that there needed to be more.

25:51.180 --> 25:57.600
By the time we did One Wing, years later, we let years elapse in between the writing of the first and second parts,

25:58.320 --> 25:59.880
we knew exactly what we were doing.

26:00.020 --> 26:03.340
We had the structure of the entire book and the role that One Wing played,

26:03.480 --> 26:08.280
both in relation to storms that came before and in relation to the fall that came after.

26:08.980 --> 26:13.340
So by then, One Wing was written, both as an individual and to Ben as part of the book.

26:14.340 --> 26:20.660
Much of the novel's action is centered on the characters flying about on wings mounted on and powered by their arms.

26:21.100 --> 26:25.920
We asked Martin about the research he did to ensure that the mechanical aspects of flying are practical.

26:26.760 --> 26:28.960
Well, I did some research on hang gliding.

26:29.720 --> 26:37.360
I got some books on it and read, so I'd be able to give the story a diverse multitude of required.

26:37.360 --> 26:45.160
We must have done fairly well in terms of accuracy because hang gliding magazines serialized storms of Windhaven after it came out.

26:46.080 --> 26:50.160
Obviously, they would not have done it if it had been too full of egregious errors.

26:53.380 --> 26:59.700
In fact, I noticed I picked up years after the original story came out in Hang Gliding Magazine.

26:59.920 --> 27:02.500
I picked up another issue of Hang Gliding Magazine on the stands.

27:02.500 --> 27:11.680
I discovered that all these people were selling Windhaven altimeters and, you know, the Windhaven brand regalosales

27:11.680 --> 27:17.100
and they become like a brand's name or something like that, so I impressed someone out there.

27:18.080 --> 27:21.200
Martin explained the plans he and Tuttle have for Windhaven.

27:21.840 --> 27:25.260
My conception of it is as a real trilogy.

27:25.260 --> 27:35.640
That is to say, neither one big book nor a series of unrelated books, but essentially we began two stories when we began Windhaven.

27:35.860 --> 27:40.660
We began the story of Maris of Wester Amberley, which ended at the end of Windhaven,

27:41.440 --> 27:46.580
and we also began a story about the social changes initiated by Maris.

27:46.780 --> 27:53.240
And that social changes rippling through the culture, affecting all sorts of things.

27:54.400 --> 27:59.500
That story is not conclusive. That story requires more volumes.

28:01.180 --> 28:08.060
But hopefully there will only be two of them that we have originally conceived.

28:09.220 --> 28:17.060
If that, if you look around ten years from now and you find that I'm working on the ninth Windhaven book with Lisa,

28:17.060 --> 28:23.160
you know, I have sold out. And hopefully that will not happen.

